         <abstract>
            <p>
               Let $G(P; Q)$ be the discrete Green's function over a discrete $h$-convex region $\omega$ of the plane; i.e., $a(P)G_{x\bar{x}}(P; Q) + c(P)G_ {y\bar{y}} (P; Q) = -\delta(P; Q)/h^2$ for $P \in \omega_h, G(P; Q) = 0$ for $P \in \delta\Omega_h$. Assume that $a(P)$ and $c(P)$ are HÃ¶lder continuous over $\Omega$ and positive. We show that $|D^{(m)}G(P; Q)| \leqq A_m/\rho^m_{PQ}$ and $|\tilde{D}^{(m)}G(P; Q)| \leqq B_md(Q)/\rho^{m + 1} _{PQ}$, where $D^{(m)}$ is an $m$th order difference quotient with respect to the components of P or Q, and $\tilde{D}^{(m)}$ denotes an $m$th order difference quotient with respect to the components of $P$. 
            </p>
          </abstract>
